            <h3>Project Overview</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-large">
            PakPulse is a cloud-based web application designed to aggregate, deliver, and crowdsource real-time local news, alerts, and updates tailored specifically for Pakistani communities. Users can receive localized notifications for traffic disruptions, weather alerts, public safety announcements, and local events, and can also contribute community posts with images.
        </p>
        <p class="text-large">
            The system delivers alerts based on user preferences and geolocation, ensuring relevance and immediacy. Built using Microsoft Azure services for hosting, data management, notifications, and user authentication, the app follows a microservices architecture using Golang backends with a React/Next.js frontend.
        </p>
    </div>

